{"repo": "AlessandroZ/LaZagne", "pull_number": 670, "instance_id": "AlessandroZ__LaZagne-670", "issue_numbers": [669], "base_commit": "a678a971c06710b0041ee5ff8488ccef9c7ce3ed", "patch": "diff --git a/.github/workflows/WinCompile.yml b/.github/workflows/WinCompile.yml\nindex 235cf2bc..822afe3e 100644\n--- a/.github/workflows/WinCompile.yml\n+++ b/.github/workflows/WinCompile.yml\n@@ -2,23 +2,30 @@ name: Build and Upload LaZagne Release\n \n on:\n   push:\n-    # Sequence of patterns matched against refs/tags\n     tags:\n-    - 'v*' # Push events to matching v*, i.e. v1.0, v20.15.10\n+      - 'v*' # Matches tags like v1.0, v20.15.10\n \n jobs:\n   build:\n \n-    runs-on: ubuntu-latest\n+    runs-on: windows-latest\n \n     steps:\n     - uses: actions/checkout@v2\n \n-    - name: Build Application\n-      uses: JackMcKew/pyinstaller-action-windows@main\n+    - name: Set up Python 3.11\n+      uses: actions/setup-python@v4\n       with:\n-        path: Windows\n-        requirements: requirements.txt\n+        python-version: 3.11\n+\n+    - name: Install Dependencies\n+      run: |\n+        pip install -r requirements.txt\n+\n+    - name: Build Executable with PyInstaller\n+      run: |\n+        cd Windows\n+        pyinstaller lazagne.spec\n \n     - name: Create Release\n       id: create_release\n@@ -38,6 +45,6 @@ jobs:\n         GITHUB_TOKEN: ${{ secrets.GITHUB_TOKEN }}\n       with:\n         upload_url: ${{ steps.create_release.outputs.upload_url }}\n-        asset_path: Windows/dist/windows/lazagne.exe\n+        asset_path: Windows/dist/lazagne.exe\n         asset_name: LaZagne.exe\n         asset_content_type: application/octet-stream\n", "test_patch": "", "problem_statement": "Release builds missing Crypto and other modules\nRelease Build v2.4.7 fails for several modules with \n\n```bash\nPS C:\\ProgramData> .\\laz.exe all -v\n|====================================================================|\n|                                                                    |\n|                        The LaZagne Project                         |\n|                                                                    |\n|                          ! BANG BANG !                             |\n|                                                                    |\n|====================================================================|\n\n########## User: nikk37 ##########\n ------------------- Pidgin passwords -----------------\n\n[!] No passwords found\n ------------------- Psi-im passwords -----------------\n\n[!] No passwords found\n\n....SNIP....\n ------------------- Ucbrowser passwords -----------------\n[-] Module UCBrowser is not used due to unresolved dependence:\nNo module named 'Crypto'\n[!] No passwords found\n\n ------------------- Sqldeveloper passwords -----------------\n[-] Module SQLDeveloper is not used due to unresolved dependence:\nNo module named 'Crypto'\n[!] No passwords found\n\n ------------------- Iiscentralcertp passwords -----------------\n[-] Module IISCentralCertP is not used due to unresolved dependence:\nNo module named 'rsa'\n[!] No passwords found\n\n ------------------- Rclone passwords -----------------\n[-] Module Rclone is not used due to unresolved dependence:\nNo module named 'Crypto'\n[!] No passwords found\n\n ------------------- Mremoteng passwords -----------------\n[-] Module mRemoteNG is not used due to unresolved dependence:\nNo module named 'Crypto'\n[!] No passwords found\n\n ------------------- Chromiumbased passwords -----------------\n[-] Module ChromiumBased is not used due to unresolved dependence:\nNo module named 'Crypto'\n[!] No passwords found\n\n ------------------- Mozilla passwords -----------------\n[-] Module Mozilla is not used due to unresolved dependence:\nNo module named 'pyasn1'\n[!] No passwords found\n\n ------------------- Ie passwords -----------------\n[!] No passwords found\n\n```\n\n\n\nThe current workflow uses `JackMcKew/pyinstaller-action-windows@main`, which adds overhead and doesn't ensure all modules are bundled.\n\n---\n\n### Suggestion\n\nI created a simplified build using `windows-latest` directly, Python 3.11, and manual install of dependencies before running `pyinstaller`:\n\n\ud83d\udcc4 https://github.com/AnvithLobo/LaZagne/blob/master/.github/workflows/WinCompile.yml\n\nThis fixes the issue. Let me know if you'd like a PR.\n\n", "hints_text": "\n\n", "all_hints_text": "Hello AnvithLobo, \n\nYes sure if you could do a PR it could be nice ! Thanks a lot. \n\n\n", "commit_urls": ["https://github.com/AlessandroZ/LaZagne/commit/abbc0ab2673dbfd9af32eed6c592c603b0e456fa", "https://github.com/AlessandroZ/LaZagne/commit/c488032ebe8f27a5bf1d9da3993ce05d3307fb6b", "https://github.com/AlessandroZ/LaZagne/commit/454ece11dbf6166ed67920f8647e71f1c993f78f"], "created_at": "2025-05-21T17:44:31Z"}
